        "type": "p",
        "text": "The impact of social anxiety on academic performance and the overall school experience can be severe. Participating in class discussions, giving required presentations, and interacting informally with peers and professors can be entirely overwhelming for students with social anxiety. This can easily lead to avoidance of certain vital courses, difficulty forming supportive study groups, and a profound sense of isolation within the broader academic community. Actively seeking support from campus counseling services, utilizing available academic accommodations, and developing effective study and communication strategies can dramatically help students manage their anxiety and truly thrive in their educational pursuits."
