        "type": "p",
        "text": "The digital age has introduced entirely new and complex layers to the experience of social anxiety. While online platforms offer valuable opportunities for connection and finding community, they can also severely exacerbate feelings of inadequacy, FOMO (fear of missing out), and the intense pressure to present a perfectly curated image. The constant, unavoidable comparison to others' seemingly flawless lives can fuel deep self-doubt and painful social comparison. Developing healthy, intentional digital habits, such as strictly limiting screen time, curating social media feeds to promote positivity rather than envy, and actively engaging in authentic offline connections, is essential for mitigating the negative impact of technology on social anxiety."
